You have the following code initializing your CV buffer:

```
#if UNITY_EDITOR
        int width = 1280;
        int height = 720;
#else
        int width = 480;
        int height = 640;
#endif

        NativeLibAdapter.InitCV(Screen.width, Screen.height);
```

Your initialization of the CV buffer is not enough to handle 800x1280, so you are likely running out of memory. It is expected that performance will dip as your size increases, as memory consumption is greater (640x480 is 4 times more data than 320x240, and therefore much more garbage collection and data processing each frame). You will need to increase your width and height to encompass the maximum resolution, or limit the pixels you retrieve from GetPixels() before feeding the data into CV.

